    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Ah! Sorbet! The food of angels!</></>Blackberries are difficult to find here but this sorbet, like others with wine, sounds like it is worth making.  I will dig up a recipe for a pomegranate, red wine and orange sorbet but pending that, here is one of my favourites. You will not like this if you dislike almonds and marzipan (strangely common in Australia) but it is a very light summer dessert which is refreshing in the extreme.</></>Marzipan Sorbet.</></>Make a syrup by boiling 600ml water with 100g sugar. Melt 30g of marzipan over a low heat in the syrup until smooth.  Allow to cool and add a few drops of orange, rose or almond water (or not, to taste). Freeze in an ice cream maker.  It will turn our like almond snow.</p>
    </div>

